Defendant Keith Lynn Harris in court, in custody.  Attorney Patrick Dennis Wait in court for Keith Lynn Harris.  Prosecuting attorney Julie D Knyszek in court for the State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: SD. 
Court finds State has complied with victim notification.  Sentencing hearing proceeded.  Statements made as to sentencing.  

AS TO COUNT 1: The court sentenced the defendant to 8 MONTHS in the House of Correction, with 9 days credit, consecutive to any other sentence.

AS TO COUNT 2: The court sentenced the defendant to 90 DAYS, with 90 DAYS credit.  THIS IS A TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

AS TO COUNT 1:  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 24 MONTHS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
- Serve 30 DAYS in the House of Correction as Condition Time, STAYED pending review;
- Batterers Intervention program,
- Mental health evaluation, comply with recommended treatment;
- AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment;
- course in anger management;
- Parenting classes;
- Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent;
- Absolute sobriety;
- No contact with victim
- Full time work/school.
- No contact with firearms;
- Provide DNA sample;
- Restitution set at $15.93 payable to MCO.

-Court waived all non-mandatory feeds.  Defendant to pay all mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges including: DNA & DV surcharges during period of probation.  Unpaid amount to convert to a civil judgment;  

*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief.
*Court advised that under 18 USC Section 922(g)(9) the defendant is prohibited from possession of a firearm and/or ammunition after conviction of a crime of domestic violence.
Probation Review Hearing scheduled for December 16, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
